url | Supported Azure OpenAI endpoints (protocol and hostname, for example: `https://aoairesource.openai.azure.com`. Useful for tools like `file_search` that can access files. | No | || name | string | The name of the vector store. | No | || expires_after | vectorStoreExpirationAfter | The expiration policy for a vector store. | No | || metadata | object | Set of 16 key-value pairs that can be attached to an object. | No | |### ResponsesStatus Code: 200Description: OK |Content-Type|Type|Description||:---|:---|:---||application/json | vectorStoreObject | A vector store is a collection of processed files can be used by the `file_search` tool.|### Examples### ExampleCreates a vector store.```HTTPPOST https://{endpoint}/openai/vector_stores?api-version=2024-05-01-preview```Responses:Status Code: 200```json{ "body": { "id": "vs_abc123", "object": "vector_store", "created_at": 1699061776, "name": "Support FAQ", "bytes": 139920, "file_counts": { "in_progress": 0, "completed": 3, "failed": 0, "cancelled": 0, "total": 3 } }}```
